// SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0 WITH LLVM-exception
//
// test/Driver/emit-ast.test — byte-frozen format golden for
// `nslc -emit=ast` (T020 of `specs/005-m2-parser/tasks.md`).
//
// **Contract anchors**:
//   - `specs/005-m2-parser/contracts/nslc-emit-ast.contract.md`
//     §"Stdout schema" (the per-line format) and §"Example" (the
//     canonical input + expected output reproduced below verbatim).
//   - FR-022 (text-only S-expression-style dump per
//     `/speckit-clarify` Q2 → Option A).
//   - FR-024 (driver wrapper inside `lib/Driver/EmitAST.cpp`,
//     `tools/nslc/main.cpp` stays ≤ 60 lines).
//   - FR-030, SC-003, SC-007 (byte-stable across runs).
//
// **Schema-stability scope**: the format is frozen byte-exactly **at
// M2** by this fixture; M3/M5/M7 may re-cut the golden in the same
// patch as a format-bumping change (see contract §"Stability"). Any
// unintentional change to the printer text format fails this
// fixture.
//
// Per Constitution Principle VIII (TDD; FR-029): this fixture lands
// BEFORE the parser implementation + driver glue. Against the
// unchanged tree at `7bc1aea`, all three commands fail:
//   - POS path:    `nslc -emit=ast` exits 2 (unknown emit stage at M1)
//                   → FileCheck pipeline errors (no AST stdout).
//   - NEG-NOINPUT: same as M1's emit-tokens — already passes (driver
//                   diagnoses missing operand at argv parse).
//   - NEG-BADSTAGE: same — covered by M1's `-emit=blarg` path.
//   - NEG-NOFILE:  M1 driver exits 3 with "could not open"; once
//                   `-emit=ast` is wired, this still must hold for
//                   `-emit=ast` because the file-open path is shared.
// Until Track D lands the parser + EmitAST glue, the POS path fails
// — that IS the failing-state evidence.
//
// ----- POSITIVE: the canonical contract example ------------------
//
// Input (per `nslc-emit-ast.contract.md` §Example):
//   module hello {
//     reg q[8] = 0;
//   }
//
// Expected stdout (verbatim from the contract; the printer asserts
// `<path>:<line>:<col>` resolution against the M1 SourceManager,
// which maps the temp file's literal path here). The temp-file path
// is created at run time so we use FileCheck regex placeholders for
// the `<path>` portion of `loc=`. Line/column coordinates ARE pinned
// — they are the schema invariant.
//
// RUN: printf 'module hello {\n  reg q[8] = 0;\n}\n' > %t.nsl
// RUN: %nslc -emit=ast %t.nsl | FileCheck %s --check-prefix=POS

// POS:      (CompilationUnit loc={{[^:]+}}:1:1-4:1
// POS-NEXT:  (ModuleBlock loc={{[^:]+}}:1:1-3:2 name=hello
// POS-NEXT:  (RegDecl loc={{[^:]+}}:2:3-2:16 name=q
// POS-NEXT:  (LiteralExpr loc={{[^:]+}}:2:9-2:10 kind=Decimal value=8)
// POS-NEXT:  (LiteralExpr loc={{[^:]+}}:2:14-2:15 kind=Decimal value=0))))

// ----- NEGATIVE 1: no input file → exit 2 ------------------------
//
// Per the contract §"Exit codes" Code 2 (driver argument parsing
// failure). M1's driver already exits 2 with "input file required";
// adding `-emit=ast` does NOT change that path.
//
// RUN: not %nslc -emit=ast 2>&1 | FileCheck %s --check-prefix=NEG-NOINPUT

// NEG-NOINPUT: input file required

// ----- NEGATIVE 2: unknown -emit stage → exit 2 ------------------
//
// Per the contract §"Exit codes" Code 2. Pre-existing M1 behavior
// for unknown stages; M2 adds `ast` to the known-stage set.
//
// RUN: not %nslc -emit=blarg %t.nsl 2>&1 | FileCheck %s --check-prefix=NEG-BADSTAGE

// NEG-BADSTAGE: unknown emit stage

// ----- NEGATIVE 3: file not found → exit 1 (per contract) --------
//
// The contract pins exit code 1 for any error-severity diagnostic
// at a pipeline stage (preprocess, lex, parse). M1's driver exits 3
// for "could not open" — M2's `-emit=ast` MUST translate the
// SourceManager open-failure to the contract's exit-1 surface for
// `-emit=ast` specifically (preserving exit 3 for `-emit=tokens`
// is M1's settled behavior). The `not` makes lit pass when nslc
// exits non-zero; we match the diagnostic text.
//
// RUN: not %nslc -emit=ast %t.nonexistent.nsl 2>&1 | FileCheck %s --check-prefix=NEG-NOFILE

// NEG-NOFILE: could not open
